3.5 Carrying out the Fitout Works
(a) The Lessee must carry out the Fitout Works:
(i) in accordance with the plans and specifications approved by the Lessor;
(ii) in a proper and workmanlike manner;
(iii) strictly in accordance with the Lessee’s Approvals and all applicable laws;
(iv) using reputable, qualified, appropriately licensed and adequately insured tradespeople which have bene approved by the Lessor; and
(v) otherwise in accordance with the Lessor’s requirements and directions from time to time.
(b) Upon completion of the Fitout Works the Lessee must:
(i) remove all materials and debris from the Premises; and
(ii) obtain a certificate of occupancy, or such other certification required to evidence that the Premises is fit for and may be used for the Permitted Use (Occupancy Certificate);
(iii) not commence trade from the Premises prior to obtaining the Occupancy Certificate; and
(iv) provide the Lessor with a copy of the Occupancy Certificate immediately on request.

